
font matter and variables:
    https://jekyllrb.com/docs/frontmatter/

add a page (use folder to specify URL)
    ├── about/
    |   └── index.html  # => http://example.com/about/
    ├── contact/
    |   └── index.html  # => http://example.com/contact/
    |── other/
    |   └── index.md    # => http://example.com/other/
    └── index.html      # => http://example.com/

add a page (use filename to specify URL)
    |-- about.html    # => http://example.com/about.html
    |-- index.html    # => http://example.com/
    |-- other.md      # => http://example.com/other.html
    └── contact.html  # => http://example.com/contact.html

data filters built in 
    default:         https://jekyllrb.com/docs/templates/
    we can add more: https://jekyllrb.com/docs/plugins/#liquid-filters

Jekyll has built in support for syntax highlighting
    https://jekyllrb.com/docs/templates/#code-snippet-highlighting

Jekyll and github pages:
    https://jekyllrb.com/docs/github-pages/

Page-specific Assets (js, css, etc)
    http://mattgemmell.com/page-specific-assets-with-jekyll/


